TOKYO, Jan. 12 (Xinhua) -- A large vehicle collided with a line of cars near an expressway exit on Thursday in central Japan's Nara Prefecture, leaving 10 injured so far, local media reported. On Thursday morning, a truck was reported to hit a passenger car waiting for a traffic light to exit the Keinawa Expressway in Shindomachi, Kashihara City from the rear, causing its collision with several other vehicles, said the the country's public broadcaster NHK, citing local police department. With about 20 vehicles damaged in the accident, about 10 people have been transported to the hospital so far, all of whom are conscious, according to the latest reports. Roads around the site were temporarily closed, and rescue operations are still ongoing.  â– 